#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:429
msgid "Hillshade"
msgstr "Ombrage"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:430
msgid ""
"Calculates the hillshade raster layer given an input Digital Terrain Model."
msgstr ""
"Calcule la couche raster d'ombres  à partir d'un modèle numérique de "
"terrain."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:433
msgid ""
"The shading of the layer is calculated according to the sun position: you "
"have the options to change both the horizontal angle (azimuth) and the "
"vertical angle (sun elevation) of the sun."
msgstr ""
"L'ombrage de la couche est calculée en fonction de la position du soleil: "
"vous avez la possibilité de modifier à la fois l'angle horizontal (azimut) "
"et l'angle vertical (élévation du soleil) du soleil."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:441
msgid "Azimuth and vertical angle"
msgstr "Azimut et angle vertical"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:443
msgid ""
"The hillshade layer contains values from 0 (complete shadow) to 255 "
"(complete sun). Hillshade is used usually to better understand the relief of"
" the area."
msgstr ""
"La couche d'ombrage contient des valeurs comprises entre 0 (ombre complète) "
"et 255 (soleil complet). L' ombrage est généralement utilisée pour mieux "
"comprendre le relief de la région."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:450
msgid "Hillshade layer with azimuth 300 and vertical angle 45"
msgstr "Couche ombrage avec azimut 300 et angle vertical 45"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:452
msgid ""
"Particularly interesting is to give the hillshade layer a transparency value"
" and overlap it with the elevation raster:"
msgstr ""
"Il est particulièrement intéressant de donner à la couche d'ombrage une "
"valeur de transparence et de la comparer avec le raster d'élévation:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:458
msgid "Overlapping the hillshade with the elevation layer"
msgstr "Comparaison de l'ombrage avec la couche d'élévation"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:481
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:672
msgid ""
"Vertical exaggeration. This parameter is useful when the Z units differ from"
" the X and Y units, for example feet and meters. You can use this parameter "
"to adjust for this. Increasing the value of this parameter will exaggerate "
"the final result (making it look more \"hilly\"). The default is 1 (no "
"exaggeration)."
msgstr ""
"Exagération verticale. Ce paramètre est utile lorsque les unités Z diffèrent"
" des unités X et Y, par exemple les pieds et les mètres. Vous pouvez "
"utiliser ce paramètre pour régler cela. Augmenter la valeur de ce paramètre "
"exagérera le résultat final (ce qui le rendra plus \"vallonné\"). La valeur "
"par défaut est 1 (pas d'exagération)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:488
msgid "**Azimuth (horizontal angle)**"
msgstr "**Azimut (angle horizontal)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:489
msgid "``AZIMUTH``"
msgstr "``AZIMUTH``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:492
msgid "Default: 300.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 300.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:493
msgid ""
"Set the horizontal angle (in degrees) of the sun (clockwise direction). "
"Range: 0 to 360. 0 is north."
msgstr ""
"Réglez l'angle horizontal (en degrés) du soleil (dans le sens des aiguilles "
"d'une montre). Plage: 0 à 360. 0 correspond au nord."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:495
msgid "**Vertical angle**"
msgstr "**Angle vertical**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:496
msgid "``V_ANGLE``"
msgstr "``V_ANGLE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:499
msgid "Default: 40.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 40.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:500
msgid ""
"Set the vertical angle (in degrees) of the sun, that is the height of the "
"sun. Values can go from 0 (minimum elevation) to 90 (maximum elevation)."
msgstr ""
"Réglez l'angle vertical (en degrés) du soleil, c'est-à-dire la hauteur du "
"soleil. Les valeurs peuvent aller de 0 (élévation minimale) à 90 (élévation "
"maximale)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:504
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:527
msgid "**Hillshade**"
msgstr "**Ombrage**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:508
msgid "Default: ``Save to temporary file``"
msgstr "Par défaut : ``Enregistrer dans un fichier temporaire``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:530
msgid "The output hillshade raster layer"
msgstr "Couche raster ombrage en sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:545
msgid "Hypsometric curves"
msgstr "Courbes hypsométriques"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:546
msgid ""
"Calculates hypsometric curves for an input Digital Elevation Model. Curves "
"are produced as CSV files in an output folder specified by the user."
msgstr ""
"Calcule les courbes hypsométriques d'un modèle numérique d'élévation. Les "
"courbes sont générées sous la forme de fichiers CSV dans un dossier de "
"sortie spécifié par l'utilisateur."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:550
msgid ""
"A hypsometric curve is a cumulative histogram of elevation values in a "
"geographical area."
msgstr ""
"Une courbe hypsométrique est un histogramme cumulatif des valeurs "
"d'élévation dans une zone géographique."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:553
msgid ""
"You can use hypsometric curves to detect differences in the landscape due to"
" the geomorphology of the territory."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez utiliser des courbes hypsométriques pour détecter les "
"différences dans le paysage dues à la géomorphologie du territoire."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:568
msgid "**DEM to analyze**"
msgstr "**MNT à analyser**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:569
msgid "``INPUT_DEM``"
msgstr "``INPUT_DEM``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:571
msgid "Digital Terrain Model raster layer to use for calculating altitudes"
msgstr ""
"Couche raster de modèle de terrain numérique à utiliser pour calculer les "
"altitudes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:573
msgid "**Boundary layer**"
msgstr "**Couche limite**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:574
msgid "``BOUNDARY_LAYER``"
msgstr "``BOUNDARY_LAYER``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:575
msgid "[vector: polygon]"
msgstr "[vecteur : polygone]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:576
msgid ""
"Polygon vector layer with boundaries of areas used to calculate hypsometric "
"curves"
msgstr ""
"Couche de vecteur de polygone avec les limites des zones utilisées pour "
"calculer les courbes hypsométriques"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:578
msgid "**Step**"
msgstr "**Étape**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:579
msgid "``STEP``"
msgstr "``STEP``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:582
msgid "Default: 100.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 100.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:583
msgid "Vertical distance between curves"
msgstr "Distance verticale entre les courbes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:584
#, python-format
msgid "**Use % of area instead of absolute value**"
msgstr "**Utiliser % de la surface au lieu de la valeur absolue**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:585
msgid "``USE_PERCENTAGE``"
msgstr "``USE_PERCENTAGE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:586
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:681
msgid "[boolean]"
msgstr "[booléen]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:588
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:683
msgid "Default: False"
msgstr "Par défaut : Faux"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:589
msgid ""
"Write area percentage to “Area” field of the CSV file instead of the "
"absolute area"
msgstr ""
"Ecrire le pourcentage de zone dans le champ \"Surface\" du fichier CSV au "
"lieu de la zone absolue"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:591
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:613
msgid "**Hypsometric curves**"
msgstr "**Courbes hypsométriques**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:592
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:614
msgid "``OUTPUT_DIRECTORY``"
msgstr "``OUTPUT_DIRECTORY``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:593
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:615
msgid "[folder]"
msgstr "[répertoire]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/algs_include.rst:3
msgid "Save to a Temporary Directory"
msgstr "Sauvegarder dans un dossier temporaire"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/algs_include.rst:4
msgid "Save to Directory"
msgstr "Sauvegarder dans le répertoire"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:616
msgid ""
"Directory containing the files with the hypsometric curves. For each feature"
" from the input vector layer, a CSV file with area and altitude values will "
"be created."
msgstr ""
"Répertoire contenant les fichiers avec les courbes hypsométriques. Pour "
"chaque entité de la couche vectorielle d'entrée, un fichier CSV avec des "
"valeurs de zone et d'altitude sera créé."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:621
msgid ""
"The file names start with ``histogram_``, followed by layer name and feature"
" ID."
msgstr ""
"Les noms de fichiers commençant par ``histogramme_``, suivis du nom de la "
"couche et de l'ID de l'entité."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:631
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:hypsometriccurves``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``qgis:hypsometriccurves``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:641
msgid "Relief"
msgstr "Relief"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:642
msgid ""
"Creates a shaded relief layer from digital elevation data. You can specify "
"the relief color manually, or you can let the algorithm choose automatically"
" all the relief classes."
msgstr ""
"Crée une couche de relief ombrée à partir des données d'élévation "
"numériques. Vous pouvez spécifier la couleur du relief manuellement ou "
"laisser l'algorithme choisir automatiquement toutes les classes de relief."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:649
msgid "Relief layer"
msgstr "Couche de relief"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:679
msgid "**Generate relief classes automatically**"
msgstr "**Générez automatiquement des classes de relief**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:680
msgid "``AUTO_COLORS``"
msgstr "``AUTO_COLORS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:684
msgid ""
"If you check this option the algorithm will create all the relief color "
"classes automatically"
msgstr ""
"Si vous cochez cette option, l'algorithme créera automatiquement toutes les "
"classes de couleurs en relief"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:686
msgid "**Relief colors**"
msgstr "**Couleurs de relief**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:689
msgid "``COLORS``"
msgstr "``COLORS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:690
msgid "[table widget]"
msgstr "[widget table]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:691
msgid ""
"Use the table widget if you want to choose the relief colors manually. You "
"can add as many color classes as you want: for each class you can choose the"
" lower and upper bound and finally by clicking on the color row you can "
"choose the color thanks to the color widget."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez le widget de tableau si vous souhaitez choisir les couleurs de "
"relief manuellement. Vous pouvez ajouter autant de classes de couleurs que "
"vous le souhaitez: pour chaque classe, vous pouvez choisir la limite "
"inférieure et supérieure et enfin en cliquant sur la ligne de couleur, vous "
"pouvez choisir la couleur grâce au widget couleur."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:701
msgid "Manually setting of relief color classes"
msgstr "Réglage manuel des classes de couleurs relief"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:703
msgid ""
"The buttons in the right side panel give you the chance to: add or remove "
"color classes, change the order of the color classes already defined, open "
"an existing file with color classes and save the current classes as file."
msgstr ""
"Les boutons dans le panneau de droite vous permettent: d'ajouter ou de "
"supprimer des classes de couleurs, de modifier l'ordre des classes de "
"couleurs déjà définies, d'ouvrir un fichier existant avec des classes de "
"couleurs et d'enregistrer les classes actuelles en tant que fichier."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:708
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:745
msgid "**Relief**"
msgstr "**Relief**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:719
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:749
msgid "**Frequency distribution**"
msgstr "**Distribution de fréquence**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:722
msgid "``FREQUENCY_DISTRIBUTION``"
msgstr "``FREQUENCY_DISTRIBUTION``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:723
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:751
msgid "[vector: table]"
msgstr "[vecteur : table]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:748
msgid "The output relief raster layer"
msgstr "Couche raster en relief de sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:752
msgid "The output frequency distribution"
msgstr "La distribution de fréquence de sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:757
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:relief``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``qgis:relief``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:767
msgid "Ruggedness index"
msgstr "Indice de rugosité"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:768
msgid ""
"Calculates the quantitative measurement of terrain heterogeneity described "
"by Riley et al. (1999). It is calculated for every location, by summarizing "
"the change in elevation within the 3x3 pixel grid."
msgstr ""
"Calcule la mesure quantitative de l'hétérogénéité du terrain décrite par "
"Riley et al. (1999). Il est calculé pour chaque emplacement, en résumant le "
"changement d'altitude dans la grille de 3x3 pixels."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:773
msgid ""
"Each pixel contains the difference in elevation from a center cell and the 8"
" cells surrounding it."
msgstr ""
"Chaque pixel contient la différence d'élévation d'une cellule centrale et "
"des 8 cellules qui l'entourent."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:779
msgid "Ruggedness layer from low (red) to high values (green)"
msgstr ""
"Couche de rugosité des valeurs faibles (rouge) aux valeurs élevées (vert)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:802
msgid ""
"Vertical exaggeration. This parameter is useful when the Z units differ from"
" the X and Y units, for example feet and meters. You can use this parameter "
"to adjust for this. Increasing the value of this parameter will exaggerate "
"the final result (making it look more rugged). The default is 1 (no "
"exaggeration)."
msgstr ""
"Exagération verticale. Ce paramètre est utile lorsque les unités Z diffèrent"
" des unités X et Y, par exemple les pieds et les mètres. Vous pouvez "
"utiliser ce paramètre pour régler cela. Augmenter la valeur de ce paramètre "
"exagérera le résultat final (ce qui le rendra plus robuste). La valeur par "
"défaut est 1 (pas d'exagération)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:809
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:832
msgid "**Ruggedness**"
msgstr "**Rugosité**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:835
msgid "The output ruggedness raster layer"
msgstr "Couche raster de rugosité en sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:850
msgid "Slope"
msgstr "Pente"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:851
msgid ""
"Calculates the slope from an input raster layer. The slope is the angle of "
"inclination of the terrain and is expressed in **degrees**."
msgstr ""
"Calcule la pente d'une couche raster en entrée. La pente est l'angle "
"d'inclinaison du terrain et s'exprime en **degrés**."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:857
msgid "Flat areas in red, steep areas in blue"
msgstr "Zones plates en rouge, zones escarpées en bleu"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:880
msgid ""
"Vertical exaggeration. This parameter is useful when the Z units differ from"
" the X and Y units, for example feet and meters. You can use this parameter "
"to adjust for this. Increasing the value of this parameter will exaggerate "
"the final result (making it steeper). The default is 1 (no exaggeration)."
msgstr ""
"Exagération verticale. Ce paramètre est utile lorsque les unités Z diffèrent"
" des unités X et Y, par exemple les pieds et les mètres. Vous pouvez "
"utiliser ce paramètre pour régler cela. Augmenter la valeur de ce paramètre "
"exagérera le résultat final (le rendant plus raide). La valeur par défaut "
"est 1 (pas d'exagération)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:887
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:910
msgid "**Slope**"
msgstr "**Pente**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:913
msgid "The output slope raster layer"
msgstr "Couche raster de pente de sortie"
